    "In the analysis of the various post-hoc tests conducted using the Games-Howell method on all possible pairs of detection groups, it is important to emphasize the significance of the largest difference (13.69 points) between the initial detection and the peak of the fifth month (t-value (151) = -3.38, p < 0.0012), which highlights the important improvement in performance.",
    "In the Planning game, 474 tasks were performed, divided into the difficulty levels shown in Table 5.",
    "Although this is the game that was given less space than the others, each level was used with satisfactory frequency.",
    "Each child was first made accustomed to the tasks required in the lower-difficulty levels and then gradually brought to perform effectively even more challenging tasks, which require more refined and complex skills.",
